The paper discusses the use of visually grounded speech data to improve query-by-example speech search, which involves natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.SD (Sound). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG), which are also possible categories.
